column4: <content>Good Shepherd by Bruegel 1565 Typical example of 1568 (chapter) : 1) composition & [?] source Raphael: Adoration; 2) Reminiscence of Bosch's Prado Adoration or one of its many copies; 3) Erhard Schön: woodcut - contrast here the shepherd does not carry the lamb on his shoulders; 4) This motive may be derived from Early Christian art (Look up Real Lexikon).</content>
